abstract: Commerce Dept reports that new single-family home sales in United States fell in June to seven-month low, dropping 6.8 percent to seasonally adjusted annual rate; figures are at odds with other data showing housing market recovery is strengthening.
lead_paragraph: Despite two straight months of declines in new home sales, new home sales were up 18.1 percent compared to June of last year.

headline.main: New Home Sales Slump to Seven-Month Low
headline.print_headline: Business Briefing; Sales of New Homes Fall to 7-Month Low
